This paper discusses the use of AI in decision-making applications and proposes a framework for optimizing AI models according to human policy makers' preferences. This topic falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses issues of fairness and bias, which could also place it in the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of considering human preferences, which could also place it in the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
